<%= lato_page_head 'Documentation', [{ label: 'Documentation' }] %>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">
    <h2 class="fs-4 mb-0">Lato CMS - Templates &amp; Components</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p>Lato CMS uses YAML configuration files to define <strong>templates</strong> and <strong>components</strong>. Templates define the structure of a page, while components define groups of fields.</p>

    <h3 class="fs-5 mt-4">Directory Structure</h3>
    <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded"><code>config/lato_cms/
  templates/
    homepage.yml
    blog_post.yml
  components/
    hero.yml
    content.yml
    sidebar.yml</code></pre>

    <h3 class="fs-5 mt-4">Installation</h3>
    <p>Run the install task to create the directory structure with example files:</p>
    <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded"><code>rails lato_cms:install:application</code></pre>

    <h3 class="fs-5 mt-4">Generating Templates &amp; Components</h3>
    <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded"><code># Generate an empty template
rails "lato_cms:generate:template[blog_post]"

# Generate a component with fields
rails "lato_cms:generate:component[hero,title:string,subtitle:textarea,image:file]"</code></pre>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">
    <h2 class="fs-4 mb-0">Template Configuration</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p>A template defines which components a page uses and in what order.</p>
    <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded"><code># config/lato_cms/templates/homepage.yml
id: homepage
name: Homepage
components:
  hero_section:                  # template_component_id (unique within template)
    component_id: hero           # references a component YAML file
    name: Hero Section           # optional, overrides the component name
  content_section:
    component_id: content
  sidebar:
    component_id: sidebar
    name: Page Sidebar</code></pre>

    <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
      <strong>Note:</strong> The <code>template_component_id</code> (the key under <code>components</code>) must be unique within the template. It identifies the specific instance of a component on the page.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">
    <h2 class="fs-4 mb-0">Component Configuration</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p>A component defines a group of fields. Below is an example showing <strong>all available field types</strong>:</p>
    <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded"><code># config/lato_cms/components/all_fields_example.yml
id: all_fields_example
name: All Field Types Example
fields:
  # ─── STRING ───────────────────────────────────────────
  # Single-line text input
  example_string:
    name: String Field
    type: string
    required: true
    settings:
      placeholder: "Enter text"
      maxlength: 255
      minlength: 3
      pattern: "[A-Za-z0-9 ]+"    # HTML5 pattern validation

  # ─── TEXTAREA ─────────────────────────────────────────
  # Multi-line plain text
  example_textarea:
    name: Textarea Field
    type: textarea
    required: false
    settings:
      rows: 4                     # number of visible rows
      placeholder: "Enter multi-line text"
      maxlength: 2000

  # ─── TEXT ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  # Rich text / HTML content
  example_text:
    name: Rich Text Field
    type: text
    required: false
    settings:
      rows: 8
      placeholder: "Enter HTML content"

  # ─── NUMBER ───────────────────────────────────────────
  # Numeric input
  example_number:
    name: Number Field
    type: number
    required: false
    settings:
      min: 0
      max: 100
      step: 1                     # use 0.01 for decimals
      placeholder: "Enter a number"

  # ─── DATE ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  # Date picker (YYYY-MM-DD)
  example_date:
    name: Date Field
    type: date
    required: false
    settings:
      min: "2024-01-01"
      max: "2030-12-31"

  # ─── DATETIME ─────────────────────────────────────────
  # Date and time picker
  example_datetime:
    name: DateTime Field
    type: datetime
    required: false
    settings:
      min: "2024-01-01T00:00"
      max: "2030-12-31T23:59"

  # ─── BOOLEAN ──────────────────────────────────────────
  # Toggle switch (true/false)
  example_boolean:
    name: Boolean Field
    type: boolean
    required: false

  # ─── SELECT ───────────────────────────────────────────
  # Single-value dropdown
  example_select:
    name: Select Field
    type: select
    required: false
    settings:
      options:
        # Option format with label and value:
        - value: option_1
          label: Option 1
        - value: option_2
          label: Option 2
        - value: option_3
          label: Option 3
        # Simple string format also works:
        # - option_1
        # - option_2

  # ─── MULTISELECT ──────────────────────────────────────
  # Multiple-value select (stored as JSON array)
  example_multiselect:
    name: Multi-Select Field
    type: multiselect
    required: false
    settings:
      options:
        - value: tag_1
          label: Tag 1
        - value: tag_2
          label: Tag 2
        - value: tag_3
          label: Tag 3
        - value: tag_4
          label: Tag 4

  # ─── COLOR ────────────────────────────────────────────
  # Color picker (hex value)
  example_color:
    name: Color Field
    type: color
    required: false

  # ─── JSON ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  # Structured JSON data (validated on save)
  example_json:
    name: JSON Field
    type: json
    required: false
    settings:
      rows: 6
      placeholder: '{"key": "value"}'

  # ─── FILE ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  # File upload (uses Active Storage)
  example_file:
    name: File Upload Field
    type: file
    required: false
    settings:
      accept: "image/*,.pdf"     # MIME types or extensions
      multiple: true             # allow multiple files (default: true)</code></pre>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">
    <h2 class="fs-4 mb-0">Field Types Reference</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <div class="table-responsive">
      <table class="table table-bordered">
        <thead class="table-light">
          <tr>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Description</th>
            <th>Stored Value</th>
            <th>Available Settings</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>string</code></td>
            <td>Single-line text input</td>
            <td>String</td>
            <td><code>placeholder</code>, <code>maxlength</code>, <code>minlength</code>, <code>pattern</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>textarea</code></td>
            <td>Multi-line plain text</td>
            <td>String</td>
            <td><code>placeholder</code>, <code>rows</code>, <code>maxlength</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>text</code></td>
            <td>Rich text / HTML content</td>
            <td>String (HTML)</td>
            <td><code>placeholder</code>, <code>rows</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>number</code></td>
            <td>Numeric input</td>
            <td>String (numeric)</td>
            <td><code>min</code>, <code>max</code>, <code>step</code>, <code>placeholder</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>date</code></td>
            <td>Date picker</td>
            <td>String (YYYY-MM-DD)</td>
            <td><code>min</code>, <code>max</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>datetime</code></td>
            <td>Date and time picker</td>
            <td>String (ISO 8601)</td>
            <td><code>min</code>, <code>max</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>boolean</code></td>
            <td>Toggle switch</td>
            <td>"true" / "false"</td>
            <td>&mdash;</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>select</code></td>
            <td>Single-value dropdown</td>
            <td>String</td>
            <td><code>options</code> (array of strings or {value, label} hashes)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>multiselect</code></td>
            <td>Multiple-value select</td>
            <td>JSON array string</td>
            <td><code>options</code> (array of strings or {value, label} hashes)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>color</code></td>
            <td>Color picker</td>
            <td>String (hex, e.g. #ff0000)</td>
            <td>&mdash;</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>json</code></td>
            <td>Structured JSON data</td>
            <td>JSON string (validated)</td>
            <td><code>rows</code>, <code>placeholder</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>file</code></td>
            <td>File upload</td>
            <td>Active Storage attachments</td>
            <td><code>accept</code> (MIME types), <code>multiple</code> (boolean)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-header">
    <h2 class="fs-4 mb-0">Configuration</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p>Configure the templates path in your initializer:</p>
    <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded"><code># config/initializers/lato_cms.rb
LatoCms.configure do |config|
  config.locales = [:en, :it]
  config.templates_path = 'config/lato_cms'  # default
end</code></pre>

    <h3 class="fs-5 mt-4">Accessing Field Values</h3>
    <p>In your frontend application, you can access page fields programmatically:</p>
    <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded"><code># Find a page
page = LatoCms::Page.find_by(permalink: '/homepage')

# Access fields
page.fields.each do |field|
  puts "#{field.field_id}: #{field.parsed_value}"
end

# Find a specific field
hero_title = page.fields.find_by(
  template_component_id: 'hero_section',
  field_id: 'title'
)
puts hero_title.parsed_value  # => "Welcome to our site"

# parsed_value returns typed values:
# - number fields return Integer or Float
# - boolean fields return true/false
# - json fields return parsed Hash/Array
# - date fields return Date objects
# - datetime fields return DateTime objects
# - multiselect fields return Array
# - file fields use .files attachment (Active Storage)

# Access file attachments
file_field = page.fields.find_by(field_id: 'background_image')
file_field.files.each do |file|
  puts file.url  # Active Storage URL
end</code></pre>
  </div>
</div>
